The paper discusses provenance analysis in databases and model checking problems for logics with full negation, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with fixed-point logics and their provenance semantics. 

cs.DB (Databases) is also a likely category as the paper discusses provenance analysis in databases. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper discusses model checking problems for logics with full negation, which is a common topic in AI research. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with semirings and their properties. 

cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the power of provenance interpretations in semirings and their relation to model-checking games.
